This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with the design of communication systems for 5G networks. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could place it in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The use of multiple communication interfaces and the formulation of an optimization problem suggest that the paper could also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The paper's focus on reliability and security could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Finally, the paper's experimental results suggest that it could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
